# Build & Release Safety

## Before changing build pipeline

1. Run `python scripts/build_icon.py` — requires `assets/integral-icon-source.png`
2. Run `.\build.ps1` and confirm `dist\Integral\Integral.exe` launches
3. Smoke test: Overview grid, log one category, Fitness Hub opens, data writes to AppData when frozen

## PyInstaller rules

- **Entry:** `personal_dev_tracker.py`
- **Bundle:** `programs/` and `assets/` via spec `datas`
- **Hidden imports:** all top-level modules (`insights.*`, `fitness.*`, `activity_grid`, `paths`, `graphs`, `fitness_graphs`)
- **Icon:** `assets/icon.ico` on EXE
- **Console:** `console=False` (windowed app)
- **Name:** `Integral` (not legacy FullSpectrumDevelopment)

## paths.py contract

Any new read-only bundled resource → add to spec `datas` and load via `bundle_dir()`.

User-writable data → `data_file()` / `user_data_dir()` only — never beside exe in Program Files as primary store.

## Release checklist

- [ ] `python -m pytest` passes
- [ ] `.\scripts\build_exe.ps1` succeeds
- [ ] Zip `dist\Integral\` → `Integral-v{VERSION}-windows.zip` (match `APP_VERSION` in `paths.py`)
- [ ] Release notes mention `%APPDATA%\Integral\data.json` backup path
- [ ] Do not attach user `data/` to release artifacts

## Release hygiene (required on every version push)

Keep **one** current release on `main` — not a pile of old zips and tags.

1. **Zip artifacts in repo root**
   - Add only `Integral-v{VERSION}-windows.zip` for the version you are shipping
   - `git rm` every older `Integral-v*-windows.zip` before committing the new one

2. **Git tags**
   - Create tag `v{VERSION}` for the release commit
   - Delete all older local tags: `git tag -l "v*" | Where-Object { $_ -ne "v{VERSION}" } | ForEach-Object { git tag -d $_ }`
   - After push, delete stale remote tags: `git push origin --delete <old-tag>` for each removed tag (or batch delete)

3. **GitHub Release** (when publishing)
   - Attach only the new zip; remove or supersede prior release assets on GitHub if applicable

4. **Commit message**
   - Use `Release v{VERSION}: <short summary>.` to match existing history

Example (replacing v0.2.8 with v0.2.9):

```powershell
git rm Integral-v0.2.8-windows.zip
Compress-Archive -Path dist\Integral\* -DestinationPath Integral-v0.2.9-windows.zip
git add Integral-v0.2.9-windows.zip paths.py CHANGELOG.md ...
git commit -m "Release v0.2.9: Windows reminders and midnight day rollover."
git tag -a v0.2.9 -m "Integral v0.2.9"
git tag -d v0.2.8
git push origin main v0.2.9
git push origin --delete v0.2.8
```

## Do not

- Commit `build/`, `dist/`, or user data (see `.gitignore`)
- Add runtime pip install to the exe — bundle dependencies at build time
- Break dev mode (`.\run.ps1`) when adjusting frozen paths
